#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:122
msgid ""
"For every couple where both spouses have at least one parent recorded, the "
"widget walks each spouse's ancestor tree up to four generations and "
"intersects the two sets. A non-empty intersection means the couple share at "
"least one common ancestor. That is the classic signature of cousin marriage "
"and pedigree collapse."
msgstr "For hvert par der begge ektefeller har minst én registrert forelder, går widgeten gjennom hver ektefelles forfedretre opp til fire generasjoner og skjærer de to settene. En ikke-tom skjæring betyr at paret deler minst én felles forfader. Det er den klassiske signaturen på et søskenbarnsekteskap og pedigree collapse."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:300
msgid ""
"For every individual in the tree the widget counts how many descendants are "
"recorded below them across all generations. A descendant reached through two "
"different grandparents is counted once per ancestor. Living individuals "
"whose webtrees record is access-restricted for the current user are excluded "
"from the podium. The ranking surfaces the people whose branches actually "
"carry the rest of the recorded lineage."
msgstr "For hver person i treet teller widgeten hvor mange etterkommere som er registrert under personen på tvers av alle generasjoner. En etterkommer nådd via to forskjellige besteforeldre telles én gang per forfader. Levende personer hvis webtrees-post er adgangsbegrenset for gjeldende bruker, utelates fra podiet. Rangeringen fremhever personene hvis grener faktisk bærer resten av den registrerte slekten."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/places.phtml:57
msgid ""
"For every individual the widget collects every distinct PLAC value that "
"appears on any of their level-1 events (BIRT, DEAT, BAPM, BURI, RESI, …) and "
"counts the unique places. Duplicates within the same individual (e.g. BIRT "
"and DEAT both in Hamburg) collapse to one place, so the count reflects "
"geographic mobility rather than how many events are recorded. The average is "
"across every individual with at least one PLAC sample; individuals with no "
"place data at all are excluded."
msgstr "For every individual the widget collects every distinct PLAC value that appears on any of their level-1 events (BIRT, DEAT, BAPM, BURI, RESI, …) and counts the unique places. Duplicates within the same individual (e.g. BIRT and DEAT both in Hamburg) collapse to one place, so the count reflects geographic mobility rather than how many events are recorded. The average is across every individual with at least one PLAC sample; individuals with no place data at all are excluded. The distribution on the right shows how those counts split across 1 / 2 / 3 / 4 / 5+ distinct places per person — a high tail signals migrant ancestors, a heavy bar at \\"

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/life-span.phtml:143
msgid ""
"For every individual with both a birth and a death date the widget computes "
"the number of days lived. A death within five years (1826 days) of birth "
"counts as under-5 mortality. The line groups those children by their birth "
"century so the historical decline becomes visible (typical 1700s value 30 to "
"40 percent, modern below 2 percent). Individuals with only a birth or only a "
"death date are silently excluded, since the rate cannot be determined "
"without both anchors. Per-century cohorts below 5 children are suppressed "
"because a single dead child would spike the line by more than 10 percentage "
"points."
msgstr "For hver person med både fødselsdato og dødsdato registrert beregnes levetiden. Et dødsfall innen fem år (1826 dager) etter fødselen telles som dødelighet for barn under 5 år. Linjen grupperer disse barna etter fødselsårhundre. Den historiske nedgangen blir dermed synlig (typisk 30 til 40 prosent på 1700-tallet, i dag under 2 prosent). Personer med kun én av de to datoene utelates. Uten begge ankerne kan raten ikke bestemmes. Århundrer med færre enn 5 registrerte barn skjules. Et enkelt dødsfall ville ellers slå linjen ut med mer enn 10 prosentpoeng."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:118
msgid ""
"For every individual, this bucket counts how many generations of descendants "
"are recorded below them in the tree. Bucket 0 = leaf (no descendants), "
"bucket N = an individual whose deepest verified descendant is N generations "
"younger."
msgstr ""
"For every individual, this bucket counts how many generations of descendants "
"are recorded below them in the tree. Bucket 0 = leaf (no descendants), "
"bucket N = an individual whose deepest verified descendant is N generations "
"younger."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:295
#, php-format
msgid ""
"For every marriage decade the bar is split into segments by the number of "
